<paragraph id="EC6D36D68039FFDEFF5E3288FDBEF997" blockId="0.[151,1101,1982,2004]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1437,151,500]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="0" pageNumber="14">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="CCC211F88039FFDEFF5E3288FDBEF997" infered="true" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="0" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName id="2BD24D558039FFDFFF5E3288FB24FFC4" authority="Mahmood &amp; Ahmed 1969: 86" authorityName="Mahmood &amp; Ahmed" authorityPageNumber="86" authorityYear="1969" box="[151,572,1982,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Benglebra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48039FFDFFF5E3288F818FFC4" box="[151,256,1982,2004]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="14">Benglebra</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation id="6D7310C78039FFDFFECF3288FB24FFC4" author="Mahmood" box="[262,572,1982,2004]" page="86" pageId="0" pageNumber="14" year="1969">
<bibRefCitation id="88434B278039FFDFFECF3288FB0FFFC4" author="Mahmood" box="[262,535,1982,2004]" pageId="0" pageNumber="14" refString="Mahmood, S. H. &amp; Ahmed, M. (1969) Studies of tribe Alebrini (Typhlocybinae: Cicadellidae) in east Pakistan: Sindh University Research Journal, 6, 85 - 91." type="journal article" year="1969">
Mahmood &amp; Ahmed 
<number id="5A1A24F18039FFDFFE293288FB0FFFC4" box="[480,535,1982,2004]" pageId="0" pageNumber="14" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="5A1A24F18039FFDFFDE93288FB24FFC4" box="[544,572,1982,2004]" pageId="0" pageNumber="14" value="86.0">86</number>
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="336988748039FFDFFD8F3289FB60FFC4" box="[582,632,1983,2004]" pageId="0" pageNumber="14">Type</typeStatus>
specis: 
<taxonomicName id="2BD24D558039FFDFFD033288FD55FFC4" authority="Mahmood &amp; Ahmed" authorityName="Mahmood &amp; Ahmed" box="[714,1101,1982,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Benglebra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alami">
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48039FFDFFD033288FA6BFFC4" box="[714,883,1982,2004]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="14">Benglebra alami</emphasis>
Mahmood &amp; Ahmed
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48038FFDEFF5E35AEF813F8A0" bold="true" box="[151,267,152,176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</emphasis>
This genus includes two species on bamboo, 
<taxonomicName id="2BD24D558038FFDEFCD735AFFA67F8A0" box="[798,895,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Benglebra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alami">
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48038FFDEFCD735AFFA67F8A0" box="[798,895,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">B. alami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2BD24D558038FFDEFC7335AFFD4BF8A0" box="[954,1107,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Benglebra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctata">
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48038FFDEFC7335AFFD4BF8A0" box="[954,1107,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">B. bipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="94C576468038FFDEFB5535A1FC07F8BF" box="[1180,1311,151,175]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
but differences between the two in the male genitalia, suggest that they may not be congeneric. The 
<typeStatus id="336988748038FFDEFB7C358BFDFDF8C5" box="[1205,1253,189,213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
species (
<taxonomicName id="2BD24D558038FFDEFA9A358AFC8BF8C4" box="[1363,1427,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Benglebra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alami">
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48038FFDEFA9A358AFC8BF8C4" box="[1363,1427,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">alami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="2BD24D558038FFDEFEAF35D6FA26F8E7" authority="Chen &amp; Yang (2007)" authorityName="Chen &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2007" box="[358,830,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mohunia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="introspina">
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48038FFDEFEAF35D6FB5DF8E8" box="[358,581,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">Mohunia introspina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="88434B278038FFDEFD8435E9FA26F8E7" author="Chen" box="[589,830,223,248]" pageId="1" pageNumber="15" refString="Chen, X. - S., Li, Z. &amp; Yang, L. (2007) Oriental bamboo leafhoppers: revision of Chinese species of Mohunia (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Mukariinae) with descriptions of new genera and new species. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 100, 366 - 374." type="journal article" year="2007">
Chen &amp; Yang (
<number id="5A1A24F18038FFDEFD3035E9FA2EF8E7" box="[761,822,223,247]" pageId="1" pageNumber="15" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, raising the prospect that the two genera may be synonyms or that the latter species belongs in 
<taxonomicName id="2BD24D558038FFDEFDBE3432FBF4F90C" box="[631,748,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Benglebra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48038FFDEFDBE3432FBF4F90C" box="[631,748,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">Benglebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The generic limits of 
<taxonomicName id="2BD24D558038FFDEFC253432FD49F90C" box="[1004,1105,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mohunia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48038FFDEFC253432FD49F90C" box="[1004,1105,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">Mohunia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear as the male genitalia of its 
<typeStatus id="336988748038FFDEFEDF341EF85EF950" box="[278,326,296,320]" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
species (
<emphasis id="DEA6EAC48038FFDEFE7D341EFB3AF950" box="[436,546,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">splendens</emphasis>
Distant) are somewhat different from many other included species in having paraphyses of the aedeagus and an apically bifurcate connective stem. Hopefully a review of the tribe being undertaken by Dr. Dai Wu (Northwest A&amp;F University, Yangling, 
<collectingCountry id="94C576468038FFDEFC9F3459FA84F997" box="[854,924,367,391]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">China</collectingCountry>
) will resolve this issue.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC6D36D68038FFDEFF0E34A2FDFAF9E4" blockId="1.[151,1437,151,500]" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">
The descriptions of both species, given below, are from the original as the 
<typeStatus id="336988748038FFDEFBD334A3FD4DF9BD" box="[1050,1109,405,429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="15">types</typeStatus>
are in poor condition. In the first, the description of the forewing venation, in square brackets, is from the original generic description. Similarly, some original figures are reproduced (for parts that are missing), in addition to our originals.
</paragraph>
